* =============================================================================
* ASAP5 PDK — ngspice-Compatible BSIM-CMG Model Wrapper Library
* =============================================================================
*
* Wraps the Arizona State ASAP5 nanosheet (GAA) BSIM-CMG models for use
* with ngspice. Original models target HSPICE; this wrapper resolves
* include paths and provides .lib/.endl corner sections.
*
* Device geometry (geomod=3, nanosheet/nanowire):
*   Lg = 16 nm, Leff = 14 nm, CGP = 44 nm
*   Nanosheet width (d) = 8 nm, height (hfin) = 32 nm
*   Sheet pitch = 24 nm, VDD = 0.7 V
*
* Model names (ASAP5 native — use directly):
*   NMOS: nmos_lvt, nmos_rvt, nmos_slvt, nmos_sram
*   PMOS: pmos_lvt, pmos_rvt, pmos_slvt, pmos_sram
*
* Multi-sheet instantiation: use m=N on the instance line.
*   Example: mn1 d g s b nmos_lvt m=2    $ 2 nanosheets
*
* Usage:
*   .lib '/Users/bruce/CLAUDE/asap5/spice/asap5_ngspice.lib' tt
*
* Corners: tt, ff, ss, sf, fs
* =============================================================================

.param asap5_vdd = 0.7

* --- Model base path ---
* All .include paths are absolute to avoid working-directory issues.


* =============================================================================
* TYPICAL-TYPICAL CORNER
* =============================================================================
